======================================================================
THE ALPHA_2 PHASE TRANSITION TABLE
======================================================================

Each alpha_1 value has a specific set of achievable alpha_2 values.
The T=10 requirement alpha_2 = (10-alpha_1)/2 always falls in the GAP.

alpha_1 | Achievable alpha_2 (n<=9) | Required alpha_2 | Status
----------------------------------------------------------------------
   10   | {2}                        |        0         | IN GAP (PROVED)
    8   | {0, 7}                     |        1         | IN GAP
    6   | {0, 1, 5}                  |        2         | IN GAP
    4   | {0, 4}                     |        3         | IN GAP
    2   | {0, 1}                     |        4         | OUT OF RANGE (PROVED)
    0   | {0}                        |        5         | OUT OF RANGE (PROVED)

The beautiful structure: the T=10 line passes through the
EXACT gap in each alpha_1 value's achievable alpha_2 spectrum.
This is a combinatorial conspiracy rooted in tournament cycle structure.
